SIMPLE: ormolu
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ormolu
<hw>or`mo*lu"</hw> <pr>(⟦ocir⟧r`m⟦osl⟧*l⟦udd⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>or moulu</ets>; <ets>or</ets> gold (L. <ets>aurum</ets>) +
<ets>moulu</ets>, p. p. of <ets>moudre</ets> to grind, to mill, L.
<ets>molere</ets>. See <er>Aureate</er>, and <er>Mill</er>.]</ety>
<def>A variety of brass made to resemble gold by the use of less zinc
and more copper in its composition than ordinary brass contains. Its
golden color is often heightened by means of lacquer of some sort, or by
use of acids. Called also <altname>mosaic gold</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>ormolu varnish</b></col>, <cd>a varnish applied to
metals, as brass, to give the appearance of gold.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ormosia</ent>⟦br⟧
